                {"$schema": "https://glama.ai/mcp/schemas/server.json",
                 "maintainers": ["laszlopere"]}
              Context (2026-06-12): submitted to glama.ai and listed, but the
              quality score stays pending — page says "create a release to enable
              scoring". A GitHub Release (v0.0.1) was published and did NOT trigger
              it: Glama wants a release created on ITS dashboard (build spec ->
              deploy -> publish), which needs maintainer access. glama.json is the
              ownership claim that grants that access, so add it (then trigger the
              build/release on Glama). mcp-tmux scored without this only because it
              already had a GitHub Release when Glama first indexed it; bytesmith
              was indexed before its release existed. See mcp-kodi TODO 11.26 for
              the same glama.json + the Dockerfile path.
              RESOLVED 2026-06-12 15:55: published Glama release 0.0.1 via the
              admin Dockerfile page (Build & Release). Working build spec:
                base image debian:trixie-slim, python 3.14
                Build steps:  ["uv pip install --system --break-system-packages '.[ethereum]'"]
                CMD arguments: ["mcp-bytesmith"]   (Glama wraps as mcp-proxy -- mcp-bytesmith)
                Placeholder params: {}   (no creds needed to start)
              GOTCHA: a plain `uv pip install --system` targets Debian's system
              python (/usr, externally-managed PEP 668) and fails fast; the
              `--break-system-packages` flag is required. Build passed in 10.6s,
              answered ListToolsRequest, then created+published the release.


