    [x] 18.5.  byte_order(data req, from_order req, to_order req,
               width opt, input_format opt=hex, output_format opt=hex)
               desc: Convert a value between host and network byte order
                     (htons/htonl/ntohs/ntohl) — i.e. swap endianness between
                     little/big, with network == big-endian.
               gate: stdlib   (pure byte reversal; no deps)
               from_order/to_order: host | little | big | network
                     (network is an alias for big; host resolves to the
                      running platform's sys.byteorder)
               width: optional fixed field size (e.g. 2/4/8) — left-pads/groups
                      the bytes before swapping; defaults to the data length
               ret: {result, from_order, to_order, width, output_format}
