               from_zone opt=UTC, to_zone opt=UTC, format_pattern opt)
               desc: Convert a timestamp between textual formats (ISO 8601 /
                     RFC 3339, RFC 2822, HTTP-date, unix epoch s/ms/us/ns,
                     strftime) and between time zones.
               gate: stdlib   (datetime + zoneinfo + email.utils; IANA tz db
                               from the OS — no deps on Linux)
               from_format/to_format: iso8601 rfc2822 http unix unix_ms
                       unix_us unix_ns | strftime (needs format_pattern)
                       | auto (from_format only — sniff iso/rfc2822/http/unix)
               from_zone: zone applied to a NAIVE input (no offset); ignored
                       when the parsed value already carries one
               to_zone:  shift the aware datetime into this zone before render
               zones:    IANA name (Europe/Budapest) | UTC | ±HH:MM offset
               ret: {result, from_format, to_format, zone, unix}


